This class is meant to represent a single atom and contains various properties such as:

pos : (numpy float array of shape (3,) ) *_np.zeros((3,), dtype=float)_*
    : A 1D array which stores the position of the atom.

vel : (numpy float array of shape (3,) ) *_np.zeros((3,), dtype=float)_*
    : A	1D array which stores the velocity of the atom.

type : (int)
     : Atom type (as defined by LAMMPS)

name : str
     : Atom element name identifier

idx  : (int)
     : Atom index

mass : (float)
     : Atom mass (grams/mole)

q    : float  *_0_*
     : Atom charge

corner : (bool) True/*_False_*
       : Is the atom a corner lattice atom?

layer  : (int) *_0_*
       : Which graphene layer does the atom belong to? The bottom layer has the index 0.

lattice : (bool) *_True*/False
	: Is the atom a part of the lattice?
	
